\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no, I got nothing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was there anyone outside the home who helped your mother look after here house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Just your grandmother might?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, well she would - she would if - she - did help occasionally if the need was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How many families were there living here actually in the Noss?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Just three families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. At that time. But mind at one time there were eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When was there eight then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh - about - 13 - I should say 1850's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But when you were going to school there were only three families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Only three, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Are you counting your grandparents as a separate family here or part of your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There was three - three crofts. Well now let me see, now I - I - was - there were - my grand - one 
- no, there were four - four here. That was - after we were divided.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So one was you and one was your grandparents and there were two other families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Two other, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How much did you help each other here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well, it there were need for help you - they always helped one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So you were friendly with each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Sometimes neighbours aren't friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no. It wasn't like Northern Ireland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 If your mother was ill how did she manage, what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - I suppose - my father did his best and that was all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You mentioned your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, oh aye, she would have come.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Apart from your grandparents here did you have any other relations living round about a bit further off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well my - our grandparents lived there - I was telling you about - that - Brey Rock there. Well they lived there, that would be about two mile from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about uncles and aunts and cousins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, they were - father away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What do you mean by further away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I mean - I had - an uncle and aunt there at Robbie Bairnson is. And another one down there at - nearer Sumburgh. And that was all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How much did you see of these relations, your grandparents here you'd see then every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But your other grandparents and the uncle and aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well - my - I say my other grandparents every day I went to school because I went there for my dinner. Too far too come here. So I - I called on them every day, we got an hour for dinner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about the uncles and aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I had an uncle and aunt there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Yes. Some. Relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But friends who were not relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh - oh yes, they had quite a few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - any place that was convenient. May be a - in a shop or a church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did your father and another have the same friends or did your mother have her friends and your father have his own friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well I suppose - there was - no difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Sometimes these friends would come visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you had people visiting what happened, would you offer them food or drink or would you just talk or would you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - they usually got food but there was no drink for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No drink, not even tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh aye, yes, tea, but I mean there was no - no alcohol.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 If you went visiting what would happen, would you just talk or would you have tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, they'd have tea but - there was no - no booze. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What else would you do when you visited - would you play games or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - we'd play a - if it was young people you might play a game of cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about the older people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - they would smoke a pipe and - keep yapping I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I've heard about people telling stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, they'd tell stories I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of stories were these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, maybe sea stories. Yes. They were most numerous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was there any singing of songs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I can't remember ever hearing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would these friends come in casually without an invitation or were they invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Both ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Many people divide society into different social clas
ses or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well there's no - there's no difference in the - in the groups here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Among the crofters you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no. They were all on the same level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There was the lairds weren't there and people like them and the ministers and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well the minister, he only came once in a blue moon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The minister lived round here didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, the minister lived - a minister for each church here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would all the people down the south end here fall into the same sort of social class or social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This would be people who were crofters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - there were a - a person who has a croft is a crofter. But a person who had no croft was a cotter. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How many people ware there who were cotters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well that's very difficult to say, I - I think - may have time to find that out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I got the impression that nearly everybody was a crofter here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, there's a few who haven't got crofts, they were classed as cotters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were they worse off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How would they make their living then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - make it by knitting and by fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Where would they get their food from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well - they'd buy their food from a shop, was a crofter here had a - here had a - a mill, there at Quendale and they ground their corn into meal and them the women baked it - meal into bread. But of course the croft - the - the cotter had to buy his meal.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So life might be rather harder for the cotters then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well probably in some cases it was but not very often I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I'm thinking of the teachers and the minister and the laird as compared to the other people like your parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No there's nothing of that here I don't think. As for the laird, we never saw 
him - except once a year. He came to collect the rent. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And you weren't taught to touch your cap or anything like that to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no. My cap went on to stop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The schoolmaster, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 In this district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, that's - that one's got me, I - I just couldn't tell you that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There wasn't anyone people looked up to or took a leading role in things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - shopkeepers, there were good few of them here. And - they served the whole district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did the shopkeepers have their own crofts as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Some of the shopkeepers had a croft but not - not all of them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But there were teachers and ministers weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They wouldn't have had crofts would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no, No. Oh well, I'd - no, they - The Church of Scotland, they had land along with a - what you call a Glebe - along with the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would the minister do that himself or would he employed someone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - he did - I can remember one minister there who did a lot herself and he had a man employed besides that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did the teachers and ministers associate with the crofters or did they associate with themselves more, were they a bit set apart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well the ministers usually went round to visit his - congregation. Members of his church. But a teachers - they didn't - I don't think they associated -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What sort of people would you say went to the church, were they different from anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did all the people have roughly the same standard of living or were some people better off than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I should say some are better off than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Who are the people who are better off then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I - ones who had money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did they get money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well that's - probably difficult. That's - depending on the fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This was a matter of luck then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Luck, yes. Yes. Yes, that's it. Chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about a family where the father had died, a family who was worse off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were there people who you can think of who were particularly ... up, families that were hard up like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You one - there was no
 National Assistance, then. So - it was - it was a bit hard for - somebody - probably they had friends would - would help them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Can you think of the other children who went to school with you, did you think that some were better off - that some were h
ard up and some were better off and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I don't think it there was much difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 People helped out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You don't think that there was one group that felt itself superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no, I never saw that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - I suppose there would be a -a ruffian here occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would you remember some families as not having such a good reputation then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I wouldn't say - any wastrels here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There weren't any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The distinction between craftsmen and labourers wouldn't apply here would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was it possible at that time to better yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Could people move up to a position of greater prosperity or status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, because you was on a very small island, you'd do - it wasn't like a huge continent, you could move somewhere else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 If somebody here wanted to get on in the world what would he have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, emigrate. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That was the answer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's the answer. And that's why they did emigrate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you remember many people emigrating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I do, I remember a lot of people emigrating.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Where did they go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 New Zeeland, Australia and America. And Canada.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you hear much from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no, well I don't think that I - it's not very much of my relations that I - that went, during my memory of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you remember people coming back to visit their relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 People did come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did they come back just temporarily or did they come to settle back here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They came temporary, most of there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you know if they sent money back, if somebody went to Canada would they send money back from Canada if they were doing well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well - yes, well you see, that's something I - I don't know because I didn't know - who sent money and who didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There weren't any close relations of yours who went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, this - a gentleman is born not made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You don't remember this expression, real gentleman or real lady, being used of anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You say a gentleman was born not made, what kind of people would count as gentlemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - nature's gentlemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It wasn't because he was born into a wealthy family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 An honest man's an honest work of God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you remember seeing a policeman around here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I could c
ount all the policeman on my fingers on one hand that ever I've seen here. That ever I've seen in this place. 'Course they've got policemen in Lerwick. Stationed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you were at school do you remember ever seeing a policeman at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes,
 once. Well it was two of the boys had had a - a row or something, I - I think, but I just can't remember what it was. But it didn't turn to - it was quite -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They'd had a fight with each other or they'd done something wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They'd truly had a fight I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What did you think of the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you have any attitude to him or any feelings about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no. You, well we never - we never hardly as a policeman here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How do you think he treated the people when he came down on this occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I never heard of any - ill treatment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And the croft was rented?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That meant the house and the land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 House and the land, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You said you saw your landlord once a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well you see our landlord stopped in - lived in the Island of Whalsay. You come past that when you - you're in \{BLANK\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7932848     }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 you see. Yes. Well, that's where he - of course there's none of that family alive now. It's run by - a company of lawyers in Edinburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So once a year you'd pay the rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Once a year, the mouth of - November.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What would happen at the rent paying, would he come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 He - came to a - a farm house, same farmhouse - every time. And stopped for - two or there days. And
 - tenants - on his estate, all - went to him and paid him the rent, yearly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And your father would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. He went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That was before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, well that was when I was - grown up. Later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 After the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 He was a through gentleman. Yes. One of nature's gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What makes you say that, how did he show that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - what you - what do you - what was it I call that fellow from - Liverpool - the - Gladstone, he clipped all their wings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They couldn't do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They couldn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They must have been some difference between landlords, some were good and some were bad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I suppose so, yes. That one was good. Nobody had any complaints ever - at any - at any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When people did have complaints about other landlords what kind of things did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - I don't know, you the - the landlord, if the tenant paid the landlord the rent he couldn't put him
 out. If he didn't pay rent, well - just get out. But I never heard that happen in my lifetime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you remember ever feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They certainly did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did you feel about that, can you say anymore about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What way did the hardship come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Times were hard and wages low.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What would make things hard, anything in particulars?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - that was just a lack of money, the - at that time there wasn't just a great lot of money flowing. Not like there is nowadays.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you feel hard up, how did you feel about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I didn't feel - not - not at that age, I was - wasn't - didn't worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did it make any difference to the family if your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I don't think, I - he was the type of man who hardly ever was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So you can't remember him ever being ill for any length of time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 If somebody was hard up, would they get help from anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Yes, there was such a things as what they called parochial relief. That was - the board - Parochial Board. They - they - you paid the rates - you paid for that every year. And any per
son who's on the Parochial - were given Parochial Relief would get some benefit. It wasn't much though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Can you remember knowing any people who did get this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, I remember one old woman here, lived here. She got it. But outside that I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 She didn't have any children to look after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no, she was a - a very old woman when I remember first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 If someone did something the people disapproved of did they show their disapproval in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh they talked - they'd talk amongst themselves but - they never shown it I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Sort of gossip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Gossip, you said it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Does rough music mean anything to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No. No, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 People going and making a noise outside other peoples houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were you given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Given lessons? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How old are you when you first went to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I was six years and - let me see - yes, six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Left here at - half past eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When would you get back here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh about - half past four I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long would it take you to get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well that's - that was a long walk a - probably - anything from a half an hour to three quarters of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well it was a public school, what they call a public school. All the children from - from - five or six to fourteen. From this - this - this area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You said you went to your grandparents for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Yes. Well it - it was only ten minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I didn't think - much of it sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I disliked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Too much discipline.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of things did you have to do then
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well - we had to - read and write. Do arithmetic. Write essays. And - sums. And that was about - well we did maybe a little physical exercise. And drawing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would there be rules you had to observe at school and that kind of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of things were you supposed to do and not to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - if - it's different now at school to what it was then. But we'd come in in the morning, first we 
had to say was the Lord's prayer. And then the register was called. Roll was called. Then you had to start on probably - geography, read, write - essay, so on
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How many teachers were there at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - some of them were all right and some of them were all wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was wrong with the ones that were wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well the ones that were wrong they were whip - stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well in a way maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
They had a - the teacher carried old fashioned strap, have you ever seen that? Bit of leather with four - tails on it. Hold up your hand and you - maybe got one or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do they still do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh it's out of date now, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was the difference between the teachers you liked and didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - I should say, a teacher - a good teacher, it's a gift.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 If they'd got a gift you mean they were interesting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - they had the gift of handing it over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did the girls get punished the same way as the boys with this strap?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were there any other punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You weren't given lines to write out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, I believe there were some lines - some writing to do like that occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you ever do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I don't think I ever did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, oh they did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What did they mean by good manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I couldn't say, it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did they emphasise other things like tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - when they spoke - they always spoke English, and we were supposed to answer back in E
nglish. I'm afraid - we haven't - we hadn't got the accent yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You say English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I suppose I speak English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So what about Scots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, well the Scots you see, they speak - they - they've got an accent different - fa
r different from the English. And then they've got the Gaelic. That's that is a language you know. Yes. But the Scot - well, he - he speaks English of course he tries but - if I heard him on the radio I'd know him
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Your teachers didn't went you to ... dialect at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, you - oh we never learned that. We couldn't speak Gaelic. They never did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I mean the Shetland dialect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well the Shetland dialect. No, no, we weren't allowed to speak that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did they meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 My mother - followed me to the school the first day I was there, that was on t
he tenth - or eleventh of May 1980 and she never - went again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They didn't have any favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What does that exactly mean, is that a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Quite often the boys fall into different kinds of groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Among themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No. There's no, - you see there would only be a
 handful there - I should say - maybe forty children at the most. Say half and half. Well ... was no - nothing to make gangs of. There was no gangsters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Sometimes you get children group together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, I know what you know, yes. No, there was nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Children who came from one part -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Form one group and children from one area form another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There wasn't any of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You left school when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Fourteen, yes. That was a - it was from six - five or six to fourteen then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No I would not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I did, yes, I went at evening classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 At the same old school. Quendale school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was that in, what did you learn then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well it was just - arithmetic - navigation - seamanship - signals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was this for then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was it for any particular question?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, But - it was from - it they went at nights, night school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How often would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Three - I think it was three nights a week. No, two night
s a week. For - arithmetic and - dictation or something of that. And - and navigation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You did gain from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of things do you think you gained?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - I passed an educational test in Davenport barracks which I wouldn't have done if I'd not been at - at school
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 While you were at school did you have any part time job, you didn't earn any money when you were a boy at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Could you tell me about your first full time jobs, when you left school what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, I worked - around the croft about - a year. Let's see - no, two years. And then I wen
t to - fishing - herring fishing as a cook and a - a rope - a loin coiler. See the - the nets - the boats carried the - fleet of herring nets, drift nets. Every net was about - well - between thirty and forty yards. They carried sixty of then. There was a
 - huge rope attached to it to pull the boat along with a captain. And I had to coil that in a locker down below. And then I had to cook all the meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This was not all the year round though?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no. Just from May 'til September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long did you go on doing that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
I was four summers there. And then summer after that I was - I was a deckhand - on a fishing boat. And then at - well the year the war broke out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So a deckhand was a bit superior to being cook and coiler was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well you tot a bit more fresh air.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It was a better job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It was a hard life to be down in a - a tarry locker, coiling away the rope. It made you - it made you a bit hard - tough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Then you went in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Could you tell me a bit about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well, I joined the Royal Naval Reserve in - 1915 - joined in 1915. I was - in Lerwick for over a year. And a Port Charlotte getting trained a squadron, rifle drill and all the rest of it. And then wa - I was drafted to Devonport. 
And I volunteered for a M.L's That's motor launches. And I was trained there for - about two months. Then I was sent to Portsmouth. And the same thing over again. Then I was drafted - I went Whale Island. Where I had to go night school. I was drafted to -
 Sheerness. January 1917. And I was there 'til the war finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What did you do after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I war in the merchant ships. And fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was this a full time job again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - the fishing was only just the same old thing during the summer months. But the merchant ships worked all the year round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So when did you go into the merchant ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I was - I went when the first war finished and I - I was mostly in the coal trade from the Continent to England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long were you in that then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I was sometimes I was ... ship I was in was in 1929 I think. ... Continent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Why did you give that up then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - the - it was - there was some strikes then, that was a job - was hard to get a job then. And - I was in
 the - in Lerwick in the building trade for two years. Two years and - then after - I had to leave there for - I - I was called up again. The - the last war. Second war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 In that time between the wars did you do much work on the croft there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh here, I don't a lot of work on the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - he - he worked the croft right up 'til - let me see - he lied in 1936.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So who looked after the croft then? Did you take it over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But you did the building trade in Lerwick as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Oh no. Not - not then. Of course I had to leave here and - and - I was called up the week before the war stated. '30, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So then you were in the Navy up 'til the end of the war were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What have you done since the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I've just been on the croft. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You've done quite a lot of different kinds of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I would have preferred, but you see, there's no - nothing to choose out here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What would you have preferred if you'd had more choice?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, I don't - I - the building trade was all right, only it didn't last
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You were in the building in the 1930's were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 '33. I was in - I was in - Portland, the south of England. And - in June 1933. I come home when I started building in Lerwick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you ever belong to a trade union or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, we had to belong to a trade union, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When was that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh God, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was this when you were in the building trade or when you went to sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Both. In - in the - merchant ship - merchant navy you've got to be in the trade union. And the building trade as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What did you first of all when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I - worked on the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How old were you when got this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Sixteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was it exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It was - a cook and a rope coiler in a fishing boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You had to cook the food for the rest of the crew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And coil up the ropes when they were drawing in the lines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Draw in the nets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How many days a week did you work at this and how many hours a day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Five. Oh you work - might work the
 clock round because .. you had to - it was all might that you - the nets were put out - nets were shot at - before dark. And before - probably before sunset. And they were hauled in again just after midnight. So - depended on how much fish you got, if yo
u had a lot of fish well - a lot of herring, you would have a long - a long day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What time would you set out them, what time would you set out from the shore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - we'd set out if we - we - in - in harbour discharging fish. We'd set out again as soon as the fish was discharged. Any tie of day.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So you'd be at it all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Almost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When did you sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well sometimes - we might have got two or three hours. But - not very often - many more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So it was very exhausting work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It was. Yes. But that was - five days a week. Well - six days a week - you went on Monday morning and we finished on Saturday night.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And then you'd rest on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, rest on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What were you paid for this?-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - the
 - my first year it was seven pounds. And - I was - three seasons after that for eight pounds. I mean - per season, for a season, that was the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long was a season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 May - from May 'til September. End of September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It was at that time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It doesn't seem very much today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh it would be no use no
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you get your keep as well, food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, I got me food. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you give any of that money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, I give some of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What did you spend the rest on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I had to be careful with it. I just can't remember anything that - clothes I suppose mostly. But - it didn't go very far, even then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So really you were getting about two pounds a month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you get any bonus of share of the catch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no, no, No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, nothing like - but they - the crew - the crew were - they worked for a share, they got - had a share of - in the - fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no. I didn't, I just - earned a wage - a lump some at the end of the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When would you get to be on the crew, how would you get to be on the crew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well you see - a person who had just left school, they wasn't fi
t for to go to be a - a crewman. So they had to await until they were physically fit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How old would you be when you could join a crew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Wall that depended on - your physic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You had to be a full grown strong chap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Before you - were a - were a crewman on the - herrings smacks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How many people were there altogether on the boat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Seven, Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How many of those would be crewmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well six and - six and the cook. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And you were the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Who did you work for then, was there a captain of the boat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well there was a - a recognized skipper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You thought he was all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did you feel about this work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well it was a matter of - you just had to like it. There was no - there was no choice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long did you go on doing that for, was it until the beginning of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I was - 1913 was my last year of that. And 1914 - I was a - one of the crewmen in a - in a - in a - in a boat. Fishing boat - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So that was the same kind of thing only your position was a better one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Well it was - I had a share of the catch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How much did you get from that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I didn'
t get much because the war came on before the season had ended. And they had to stop fishing when the war started. I think I had about fourteen pound maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So it was quite a bit more anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Quite a bit more.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I was reading about the 
fishing this morning in the library at Lerwick and they said 1985 was a sort of peak year and after that it rather tailed off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It didn't seem to say very well why it tailed off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well there's nobody can do anything about that you see, because - if the fish is not there well - you can't get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The fish weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I - I don\rquote 
t suppose they were if they couldn't get them, a huge fleet of English and Scotch vessels fishing from Shetland. Besides foreigners. Germans and Dutchmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So it may have been over fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
No, no, I don't think it was over fishing because - they didn't always fish the; same amount of the year, I mean - fish wasn't so - didn't seem to be so plentiful - every the year the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The fish changed their habits or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Something - well, somebody - nobody knows but they didn't get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But it wasn't a case of the market for the fish disappearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no, no. The market was all right then. Until after the war and then - the fishing market finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When was it you joined the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 January 1915.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You said quite a lot about that on the last tape didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But how much did you get paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I got - our wages were - twenty-one shillings a week to start with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about towards the end of the war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well that's rather difficult because you - you get so much - I - I couldn't - I couldn't - I can't remember what that was but it was a bit more but not a great lot. Oh well- a little over thirty bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you were in the Navy did you send money home to your parents or did you have it all to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I had it all to me - well, no, I - allotted - small amount - my father drew - a few shillings in the week, 
I had to allot something before he could get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did you like being in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - sometimes all right and sometimes all wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Up and down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Up and down, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you were in the navy did you get any holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, oh yes. Got leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How much leave would you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well - probably leave three times a year. You got Christmas leave. And - well it's all - that's something that wasn't - you couldn't never tell what you - there was none - you - you worked - Christmas leave and - Easter leave I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would you come back to the Shetlands then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you were fishing, the rest of the year you would work on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You didn't have any other jobs at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How we'-l talk about the jobs you had after the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, after the war finished I was in a - I was in the merchant ships.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Up to when was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - the war finished in - 1918. ... was at the fishing. For a year or two.
 Then I went back to the - merchant navy again, worked in colliers. Ran from - north of England to - south of England and sometimes - often to the continent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long were you on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - 1928 I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And then you did a bit of work in the building trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were there any other jobs you had in the 1930's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 '30's No. I don't think so. Except when I was crafting or something like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Then you went in the navy again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I was - again. In the second war. More or less a week before the war started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And since the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I've been crofting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 -Just full time crafting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you ever have any training or apprenticeship for any of these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you were in the merchant navy you did belong to a union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes, you had to belong to a union before you could get a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you take part in any union activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I did not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Employers - well you see the - the - in the Merchant Navy the - the employers - is ashore, I mean, in an office. When you're on board ship it's the - ship's officers that - that has you in charge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you feel that the seamen and the ships' officers and the same interests or were there conflicts between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, there was no conflict no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 We take the period before the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But you had that last night didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Except when you were actually fishing you went on living at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did going to work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 With your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you spend Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Sunday? You mean, here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When you left school did you still go on going to Sunday school and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I left Sunday school - stopped going to Sunday school when I was - when I left the day school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So your Sundays were a bit different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Any other difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I went to church instead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you take any interest in politics before the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I did not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - maybe to a dance or - to- something - some entertainment or - not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 With anyone particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you make any new friends after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I - I went t- the night school during the winter sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you make any new friends after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There was no new friends to make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I shouldn't say any special ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You didn't have any girlfriends, special girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 After you'd left school did your parents expect to know where you were or did they expect you to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no. I was my own boss. I come home any time I wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about your brothers job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well - well he was fishing too and he was in the Merchant ship.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Is he still alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no. He died in 1936.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So he was fishing and in the merchant navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Could I ask about your children as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How many children have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 One son and two daughters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This is your son here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Could you say what work you've done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 (Son) Well I - I was home for about - a year and a half or two 
years after I left school. And then I went to work in Lerwick. For - for firm of butchers. Was there for about four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You helped in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. I - well I was serving an apprentice. And then I - I left there and came to work for the - fi
rm over here at the other side of the island.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Doing what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
The same thing, in the butchery. And - it was near home so I was able to get home every night. And after that - I was there for about - four and a half years and than I - I left there and went to the - aerodrome fire service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long have you been in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I've been with them now for about - over six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That brings us up to the present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Right up to the present yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 My oldest one was at - a housekeeper to a
 schoolteacher. A local schoolteacher. Wasn't that right John. Oh yes, she cooked - a cook in the school canteen. Until she married. And then she - she married in farmer and settled down at - they've got the Quendale farm now and they've got whole family.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's where they make those sheepskins that I've heard about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Same direction - yes. That's right. Well - few hundred yards from them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So how she's a full time farmer's wife
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. And the other daughter now is - sixteen. No, fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So she's just about leaving school now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 She's finished with school. She's in a - guest house now in Sumburgh, nor far from - Meadowvale, that's right. That's her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's your second daughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And her second daughter. Grand daughter, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This is the eldest daughter of your daughter at Quendale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
That's right. And - my other daughter went to Lerwick and she served her time in a - dressmaking. And then she married. And she's - has two daughter's now living in Levenwick, they've got a new house of their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What does her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
He's a joiner. At one time it's what they called running. A rig. Means ridge. You had - suppose there's four - four crofters. You had a - a ridge here, I have another here and another one h
ere - another one here. And - I have one have and you and he has this one and another man has that one. Start over here with another four. And so on. That's what they call a runrig. And - that was the - an old fashioned missive, rig means ridge, it wasn't
 much more than a - about the width of this floor, well each of that - rigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was this arable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Arable, yes. Yes. And - you - never changed that. Everyman kept his own. But - that - the - the grazing, it was laid off in small pieces. If you had - y
ou - if I had that piece, this here, and you had that piece - you - we would change round. And that was the - method they carried on with the grazing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Who did you change round among just the people here at Ness?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well suppose there were eight neighbours. That eight changed round through the year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long would that system go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That went on until - 1902.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well got - called in a man - a self educated man who could make a map, from - North Mainland in 
Shetland and - he divided the whole in - in big pieces. And - then everyman kept that big piece of himself. So that's the - when they call the redivision of land took place, 1902.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was what just for this part down here, Dunrossness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no. It was just for this township, not - not the district, just the township. Township of Noss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was the reason for the changeover?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well the reason was to make it easy, you could fence in a big - piece of land whereby if you had no bother changing ro
und all the time, it wasn't so - it wasn't big enough - you couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How common was this changing round system?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 It was - common, as far as I know, all over Shetland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did it stay on longer down here at Noss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh that I couldn't t
ell you but I - you see, I didn't know - I expect this was probably one of the last places who did - stop that. Changing round of the grassland. But there were two hills, one there and one there and they - the - there was no restrictions really - every pe
rson who had a claim could put in as many sheep as he liked. Of course it could be overstocked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes there any check on overstocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There's a check now. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was there in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 There wasn't not any than.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 ... there were three categories of land really, arable, grassland which was rotated and - the open hill land.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Which was free to everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's right. Free to everybody who had a claim. I mean, there were eight neighbours here and
 probably a few round about - about on the same estate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Would having a croft mean you had a claim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, oh yes. If you had a croft in that area. And the came - belonging to the same landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did the landlord have any say in this redistribution of the land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
No, that - I don't think he had any say in it - this red vision of land because - he got his rent and he didn't - didn't matter to him how it was divided. Only if a dispute arose he - he did have say then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Could you say something about this black house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well - the black house was a - a house with a fife - no fireplace - no chimney. And - a stone set up about eighteen inches from the gable end of the house and the fire set up to that and a - a beam leading across the house 
with a chain attached to it and a hook in - hooking on a kettle and - was a hole in the roof and the smoke used to get through this hole in the roof.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Why was it called a black house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well you'd seen inside of it you wouldn't - you would know. Cr
eated soot. The smoke. Well some went out the door and some went out - up the whole in the roof. And some - well you would say soot you know, that soot. Smoke create soots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Up to what time was his black house here occupied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 1904.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well the person who lived in it had to go to a - home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Who was this person?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 An old woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 She was rather exceptional, there weren't many of these black houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no. It was only when there wasn't - at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But earlier on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh they were all black houses at one time. I don't know just a bit whether there was a quern. It's - it's hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Could you say what it was used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, it was - used for - you had a - the grain, the coats or the ber
e and it had to be ground - it had to be - dried very hard in a kettle over the fire. Before it was - light that's the one very light like they are on the - ones that they crush. Before you could grind it, it had to be dried very hard. And - they - they g
round it - they dried it, ground it and - made bread with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Can you remember this quern being used yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I - the only time I ever saw it used was, as I told you, for brewing ale.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about the hollowed out stone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well I never saw that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What's it a called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Knocking stane. Stane. Scotch for stone. Knocking stane. Knocking stane, you know, you've a mallet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This is a deeply hollowed out stone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Where people would grind with a mallet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You had to dry that very hard too before it could thresh. And they made some sort of broth out of that, what they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This was never in use in your lifetime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Never, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about the grain drying thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's a kiln. Yes, well - the - the
y - a stick or I say a thing like a pit prop, you probably know what I mean. Yes. Across - a thing about that size across the kiln. Than you laid on - there's a ledge right along the - for the end of a stick to rest on. They laid on thin small sticks on t
o
p of that. Then they laid on straw, drawn straws, oat straw. And laid corn on top of that and put a fire on. A - a huge fire, we got plenty of grass. And that probably had to do - depended on the wind, how much draft was on it. And that had to be - be dri
ed hard too. And then sent to the mill, it was a - there's a communal - Quendale form. It's not in use now but up to the war finished it was in use.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Up 'til the last war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes, up 'til the last war finished. I fetched the last meal from there - ju
st about the time the war finished. And it'll never be used again
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 You went on using the kiln did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No. Not here. They - they had a kiln at Quendale where they dried it there, and they made a better - it was handier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But basically it was the same kind of kiln as you had here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The same - the same method but a different - they didn't have any straw bedding. They had - cast iron plates or something like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you remember this kiln being used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh yes. Remember, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Up to what time did it go on being used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well I never used the kiln, I never - I never used - but - my father used it. Well I should say up 'til - '30 - 19 - probably 1930. There was a lamp they and - you've been in the museum - several probably. That
 me, yes, you've been in any Scotland? Oh. Well I don't know whether they have them in England but - it's a very, very old - method. It's what they call - me - the local name here was a collie. But the - the official name is crusoe. I couldn't give you a 
d
escription of - a thing like a - it's a - about the length of that see, it's a flat receptacle like. It's got a - a spout on it sort of thing like that, flat, and then it has a - it's made of iron course. I think there's two of them, one above the fire. A
n
d you form them together with an iron - plate, probably made by a blacksmith. And the oil - the fish oil it burned - they put it in the hall, about probably an inch and a half deep, and - they burnt fish oil. And there was a - a wick, I - I think the wick
 was made of - some sort of fibre, I couldn\rquote t tell, you, maybe a piece of cloth or something of that. But it was a - there was a lot of smoke from it. It didn't show much light.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When did people use this kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I'll tell you, before 
the days of paraffin. When this place was first inhabited they didn't know what paraffin was. And they had invented something. Well of course they did it in more places than this, they did it in the Highlands. The - they lit this piece of - that was fish 
oil they burnt, they had it. And if anybody who had no men going to the fishing - just had to do without - with nobody - only - only light they got was from the peat fire. So you can imagine what like it was on a dark winter night. All the light you had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And with the long nights here too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Long night too. Four o'clock 'til - nine o'clock the allowing morning. Mid winter. Well, this did show a bit of light, but - nowadays you would almost need another lamp to see it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When did the paraffin come in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well I couldn't give you that date because I don't know it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But do you remember these being used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, I never remember them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Do you know how they got the fish oil out of the fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh the livers. They - they melted the liver and got the oil from the liver. You've seen cod liver oil I suppose? Well that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But this was done by people individually, it wasn't a factory that did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, well the fishermen you see, they kept the liver, they kept an awful lo
t to last then over the winter. They melted the liver into oil. And - used this for the fuel for the lamp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was the name again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Collie. You - when you - when you go away again? What day? Oh, Thursday. Look in the museum and ask the curator, 
Tom Henderson, if he's got a collie - a crusoe or a collie - an old fashioned lamp. He'll show you one - if he's got it. I can't remember seeing it there. But I have seen one in a museum. They have them in the Royal Scottish museum in Edinburgh. Oh well y
ou'll see it then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The kind of boats there are in that picture, these were for line fishing and they were inshore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's for handline, no, handline that you draw probably one or two fish on it, but I - also for - long lines then. Maybe a - well
 a few hundred fathoms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long did these go in use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long did they go? Well they - they went right up 'til 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What were they called exactly.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This - well this parish we're in now is - Dunrossness, well it's known all over Shet
land as the Ness. A point. And - that was at Ness yawl. Ness yawl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of fish were caught with these?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 The blackjack. Mostly, and halibut. But that - they got the halibut on the long lines. And blackjack was caught on the handline. And - c
od and ling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Were these sold or did you eat them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Oh the - that was sold, you could see the - the - taking the guts out of the fish there, gutting and taking the heads of and they - they were mainly employed for splitting the fish and then salti
ng the fish and then drying it. Curing it. Then it was shipped to probably to - I think Ireland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about the fish you kept for yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh well, you - the fisherman- the fish there they were - practical men at gutting and splitting fish, t
hey - they always some for them - for their own use for winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did they dry it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well, they hung it in the roof to dry it. Until it was dry and then stored it away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And that supplied your fish supply for winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was it blackjack mostly that was dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Blackjack, yes. He - he was - he made a tasty fish too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Did you like dried fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 I thought it might be a bit hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, it was - but not - no, it's not hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about the herring fishing, how was that carried out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well the herring you see was - now - at one time - you know where just is, Eltasound. Well - there's a huge fishing industry carried on there. There was - another station - other stations in Yell. In Lerwick. In Sa
ndwick. In Levenwick and Grutness where the boats are. And then you come round to Scalloway and right round the west coat of Shetland there were other - Romas Voe. And all that was - there was hundreds of - I - I've got it all - all down my side, just can
'
t know where they are but the statistics of the herring fishing in Shetland. And - I - well it's - there's a great number of them, I really don't know. And Lerwick of course was the biggest place. But that place Altasound - in the summer time was a very -
 a hive of industry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What kind of boats did they use,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - boats about - forty - fifty feet long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What were they called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well just a herring fish - herring fishing - smacks, herring fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 These replaced the sixerns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No,
 this maybe some sixerns were going at that - that - had nothing to do with the sixereen. The sixereens maybe at the same time for bigger fish. But this herring fishing, they carried nothing but the herring, boats, they only carried herring nets you see. 
What you call drift nets. Maybe - old boats - old fashioned boats, maybe thirty or forty feet, maybe sixty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 This was the kind of boats you went in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Until - and then they had - at one time they - they had no - they had - well they finished wi
th that old steam boat, they had a steam boiler - ... power from the - with a capstan. From the - from the boiler. Thorns the older type they had hand capstan, they had to - wind by band.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 They had to wind in the nests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. The - the rope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But there were sailing ships?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well there was - vessels with - big mast a mainsail, a foresail and a - a jib.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 And no engine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No, no, no engine no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When did engines come into the herring fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - I think the first motor ve
ssel I saw was 1910. That was a - at that same place for - was built - was built in the South. Vessel specially built for line fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Tell me about the Shetland spade then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - Shetland spade, we've gone one but I'm sorry it's not here, it's very down in the field there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What was it used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
What every - everything, cultivate on the land and digging up potatoes and whatever you want to do. Get any turf you'll have to use that. You - which - bigger bit bigger then but it was that 
shape you see and then you had a wooden handle with a - a wooden handle with another stick of wood sticking out to put your foot on. Cross piece. I think you'll see them in the museum as well, I used to see one in the museum. I should think so. That was m
ade by the local blacksmiths you see. And then the parson who used it, he - he took it home and put a wooden handle to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was this used for cutting the peats as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well - oh that's another one. That one has a - tushkar. Used them in the - we 
used them here yet and they use them in the highlands . Here. It's about the same length as this spade handle. Now, that blade cuts the - the moor, the peat moor. And that iron up to say there - if I'd known earlier I could have shown you one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Was all the digging done using the Shetland spade?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. All the digging done by them, nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When did people start having ploughs them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh I - I just couldn't - I couldn't give you the exact date but - I should say - roughly - about - over eighty year ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 But you remember these spades being used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
They never used - they never depended on the spade here, they had a - ploughs here - as far back as I can remember. But - there was maybe a few in outlying districts still used the spade but - never here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 When the men went fishing in the summer who looked after the crofts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well you see, the - the men stopped at home until - they had finished - sowing of the seed and the planting of the - we call it taties. And - then they had
 to go. And the women looked after the croft. They hoed the cabbage and - did all the - drying of the peats. The men cut the peats and worked their land and made it all ready. Put in the seed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What about the hay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Well the hay, the hay never come
 on 'til - that's meadow hay, until August. It'd be - but the twelfth of August was - in those days. Were about the finish of the fishing season. Then they would cut the hay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 As soon as the men came back from fishing they'd do the hay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Yes. Yes. And then - they harvest - the corn was cut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 A little later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 That's right. You've heard of a deep freeze, a fridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 What's the equivalent of that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Here, at one time, it was a skjo. Well - it's - if it had been daylight and we'
d had a car I could show - I could have shown you where there was one or two. A long way from here. A skjo - when - well now before this when you tried to keep your fish without salt, keep it fresh, without salt, they - here's a place there at - south of 
Q
uendale, it's on that picture but it's - you can't see it, I mean, on the other side of that bay. They - what they call a skjo, it's about - say, five feet square we shall say. And it's solid rock, there was no grass or no nothing and they - that was abou
t
 maybe that high, they rooted it with turf. Had a door on it and when they laid their fish in there. No - it kept longer - without salt. And then they had - when they couldn't - the weather was bad they couldn't get to sea for any fish, they had - a store
 of fish in the skjo.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How long would it keep there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well that's all - you see that depended on the time of the year and the weather. But that is true. If - if I was - had that place now I could show you where that place was and show you the - well you see the foundation of it, some of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How was it that it could keep it much longer like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 
Well you see, they rose to their occasion. Now if you put that in a - in a - in a - in a sort of a place of earth - it - it's not so cold as the
 solid rock. There's not earth and no grass round it. A rock must - if it's covered it'll keep cold. And they rose to their occasion. Of course it's a big room you see, the hole's - maybe you could put your foot through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 So the wind blew through it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Wind blew though it, yes, that's why it was called skjo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 These went on being used until recently then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 Oh no, I never remember that. Only - that's - that's - as I say, it's a relic of the past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid331150 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 How did people keep things cool before fridges came in then? Was there any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12993156 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4938996\charrsid7932848 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10714558\charrsid7932848 
\par }}